text:
You can use Smartsheet for this. Anyone in the org can be invited to view or edit cell content, you only need licenses for the people who are building the project spreadsheet itself. They have grid, Gantt, calendar and card views, and you can easily create sub-tasks and dependencies with a dynamic timeline. Tons of workflows to set up automated reminders, connect different sheets (e.g. your editorial calendar with an industry-specific campaign plan), send you weekly status reports, etc.

I’m a huge Smartsheet stan, obviously. Our three main uses are to manage our editorial calendar, to manage our video team’s production, and to plan our campaign timelines and deliverables (which we think manage via cards in Jira—however, if we as an org weren’t tied to Jira, that + revisions/feedback could all be done in Smartsheet :slightly_smiling_face: ).
